# ~/.claude: only CLAUDE.md and hooks/*.sh are tracked. Everything else is
# machine-local, churny, or private (transcripts, sessions, tokens) and must
# never sync. chezmoi only manages files you explicitly `chezmoi add`, so these
# are belt-and-suspenders against an accidental wholesale `chezmoi add ~/.claude`.
